### 2.3 Panel System

Panels slide in from the right, covering the full screen. Each panel has:
- A header with title + back button (`← Back`)
- Full-screen content area
- Panels stack: opening a panel from within a panel pushes to stack

```javascript
// Panel management
const panelStack = [];

function openPanel(panelId) {
  const panel = document.querySelector(`.panel[data-panel="${panelId}"]`);
  panel.classList.add('open');
  panelStack.push(panelId);
  document.getElementById('panel-container').classList.add('has-panel');
}

function closePanel() {
  const current = panelStack.pop();
  document.querySelector(`.panel[data-panel="${current}"]`).classList.remove('open');
  if (panelStack.length === 0) {
    document.getElementById('panel-container').classList.remove('has-panel');
  }
}

function closeAllPanels() {
  panelStack.forEach(id => {
    document.querySelector(`.panel[data-panel="${id}"]`).classList.remove('open');
  });
  panelStack.length = 0;
  document.getElementById('panel-container').classList.remove('has-panel');
}
```

### 2.4 How Guide Content Gets Merged

The guide has 5 sections: Getting Started, For DM, For Players, Tips, FAQ.

**Approach:** DON'T dump all guide text into the app. Instead:

1. **Contextual tooltips** — Small `?` icons next to complex features. Tap → shows a tooltip/popover with the relevant guide snippet.
2. **Guide panel** in More tab — A searchable, collapsible guide for people who want to read everything. Uses the same content from `guide.html` but rendered as collapsible accordions inside a slide-in panel.
3. **Onboarding hints** — First-time DM/player sees 3-step overlay ("Tap dice to roll", "Your party is here", etc.) — dismissable, never shown again (stored in localStorage).

**Content mapping:**
| Guide Section | New Location |
|---------------|-------------|
| Getting Started | Onboarding flow (built into login screen) |
| For the DM | Tooltips on DM-only features + Guide panel |
| For Players | Tooltips on player features + Guide panel |
| Tips & Tricks | Guide panel "Tips" section |
| FAQ | Guide panel "FAQ" section (collapsible) |

### 2.5 How Flow Content Gets Merged

`flow.html` is developer/architecture documentation. It shows the data flow, access matrix, and tech stack.

**Approach:** This is NOT user-facing. Don't merge it into the app UI.

- **Archive** `flow.html` to `docs/flow.html` (or keep it where it is)
- The access matrix info is useful internally — encode it as JS constants in `app.js`:
  ```javascript
  const ROLE_PERMISSIONS = {
    dm: ['party', 'manage', 'initiative-control', 'notes', 'ai-summary', 'npcs', 'monsters', 'encounters', 'wiki-edit', 'map-edit', 'quest-gen', 'trap-gen'],
    player: ['character-edit-own', 'dice', 'initiative-view', 'spells', 'journal', 'ai-chat'],
    spectator: ['initiative-view', 'dice-view']
  };
